HEADWORD: Ninepence
<hw>Nine"pence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ninepences</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An old
English silver coin, worth nine pence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A New England name for the Spanish real, a coin
formerly current in the United States, as valued at twelve and a half
cents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ninepenny</ent>⟦br⟧
